{
  "texts": [
    "It is not sufficient for models to merely outperform previous models.",
    "Rather, performance of LLMs should be compared with the performance of human clinicians, both of which should be compared against gold-standard, evidencebased care.",
    "When LLMs are tasked with mental health evaluation, their ability to predict scores on reliable and valid mental health assessments should be tested, and LLMs should meet human clinician performance in diagnostic accuracy.",
    "When LLMs are tasked with aiding mental health intervention delivery, their ability to detect, support, and engage in EBP is critical.",
    "Additional criteria to consider when evaluating the accuracy of LLMs include the level of agreement between human clinicians and LLMs, metrics of effect size rather than only statistical significance, and the balance of sensitivity and specificity in making diagnostic predictions.LLMs should communicate confidence in the accuracy of generated output and limit or withhold output when confidence is lacking [58]."
  ]
}